196
00:26:32,194 --> 00:26:41,478
[SPEAKER_10]: And as you heard from that message from Michelle Bachelet as well, we must include them as they will inherit the world that the UN and all of us create.

197
00:26:42,501 --> 00:26:48,047
[SPEAKER_10]: But first, of course, we are gathered here on a very significant anniversary for Korea.

198
00:26:48,568 --> 00:26:52,071
[SPEAKER_10]: And of course, we know many of us from Korea will know what that is.

199
00:26:52,131 --> 00:26:54,254
[SPEAKER_10]: And that was in 1950.

200
00:26:54,334 --> 00:26:58,098
[SPEAKER_10]: This was the day of the outbreak of the Korean War.

201
00:26:58,538 --> 00:27:04,424
[SPEAKER_10]: Of course, the legacy of that makes us even more determined to achieve peace.

202
00:27:05,085 --> 00:27:20,382
